objectives.name: Primary Objective 1
objectives.description: To evaluate the efficacy of cariprazine 1.5 mg/day and 3 mg/day compared with placebo as an adjunctive treatment to ADT in patients with MDD who have had an inadequate response to antidepressants alone.

endpoints.name: Endpoint 1
endpoints.description: Change from baseline to Week 6 in the Montgomery-Åsberg Depression Rating Scale (MADRS) total score.

endpoints.name: Endpoint 2
endpoints.description: Change from baseline in the CGI-S score.

endpoints.name: Endpoint 5
endpoints.description: MADRS response (≥ 50% reduction from baseline in MADRS total score).

endpoints.name: Endpoint 7
endpoints.description: Change from baseline in the HAMD-17 total score.

endpoints.name: Endpoint 8
endpoints.description: Change from baseline in the HAM-A total score.

objectives.name: Safety Objective 2
objectives.description: To evaluate the  safety and tolerability of cariprazine 1.5 mg/day and 3 mg/day compared with placebo as an adjunctive treatment to ADT in patients with MDD who have had an inadequate response to antidepressants alone.

endpoints.name: Endpoint 1
endpoints.description: The safety parameters will include AEs, clinical laboratory parameters, vital signs, ECG parameters, EPS scales, the C-SSRS and the YMRS..

activities.name: Verified Clinical Trials (VCT) Check
activities.label: Verified Clinical Trials (VCT) Check
activities.description: Verified Clinical Trials (VCT) is a global network used to ensure the safety of research participants and the integrity of clinical trial data. VCT prevents individuals from enrolling in multiple studies simultaneously, which can compromise safety and data quality. By verifying participant eligibility and preventing duplicate enrollments, VCT enhances the reliability of clinical trials, supporting the development of safe and effective medical treatments

activities.name: Vital Signs
activities.label: Vital Signs
activities.description: This panel was created to collect the set of vital sign observations that was originally defined by HITSP and called the "Vital Sign Result Value Set" in the C80 Clinical Document and Message Terminology Component (Value Set OID: 2.16.840.1.113883.3.88.12.80.62), but it is not limited for use in that context. This collection includes the standard vital sign measurements (heart and respiratory rate, blood pressure and body temperature) along with measurements for height, weight, head circumference (OFC), and oximetry.

activities.name: SAFER Criteria Inventory
activities.label: SAFER Criteria Inventory
activities.description: The SAFER criteria inventory is a clinician-rated scale that is used to facilitate the identification of appropriate and valid patients for clinical trials

activities.name: Young Mania Rating Scale (YMRS)
activities.label: Young Mania Rating Scale (YMRS)
activities.description: Young Mania Rating Scale (YMRS) is an eleven-item multiple-choice diagnostic questionnaire that psychiatrists use to measure the presence and severity of mania and associated symptoms.

activities.name: Barnes Akathisia Rating Scale (BARS)
activities.label: Barnes Akathisia Rating Scale (BARS)
activities.description: The Barnes Akathisia Scale (BAS or BARS) is a rating scale that is administered by healthcare providers like physicians, and nurse practitioners to assess the severity of drug-induced akathisia (It follows diagnostic criteria for pseudo-akathisia, and mild, moderate, and severe akathisia)

activities.name: Clinical Global Impression of Severity (CGI-S)
activities.label: Clinical Global Impression of Severity (CGI-S)
activities.description: The Clinical Global Impression of Severity Questionnaire is the clinician-reported analogue of the PGIS.
